  "optimization_notes": "Root cause is a storage-level key-width mismatch in the dominant scan (Category E): grouping by a tiny composite domain still reads two 32-bit dictionary code columns per row, inflating memory traffic in a bandwidth-bound path. The plan adds a persistent row-aligned composite uint8 key for (l_returnflag,l_linestatus), keeps existing scaled numeric columns and zonemap-driven shipdate filtering, and uses direct-array aggregation keyed by combo code with finalize-time keymap decode to preserve grouping and sort semantics while reducing scan bytes.",
